OL,3,CYork and Hull amongst worst areas for
OL,4,Cpharmacy closures
OL,6,FOlivier Picard, NPA chair, said: "Many
OL,7,Fof our members are borrowing money to
OL,8,Fpay their running costs. They're
OL,9,Fcashing their pensions early and
OL,10,Funfortunately often can't meet ends
OL,11,Fand as a result close their
OL,12,Fpharmacies."
OL,14,FManuel Mestre Valdes, is a fourth
OL,15,Fgeneration pharmacist based in Hull.
OL,16,FHe said: "The pharmacies that are
OL,17,Fstaying open are suffering tremendous
OL,18,Fpressure to manage the workload of all
OL,19,Fthe other pharmacies closing.
